15 (6) The increase in nighttime robberies and other crimes at
16 retail convenience stores heightens the risk of danger, exposure to violent
17 incidents, and crime to consumers and employees;
18 (7) Some states have mandated certain minimum security measures
19 at retail convenience stores to enhance and protect customers and employees
20 of convenience stores during the nighttime hours, including Florida, Maine,
21 and New Mexico; and
22 (8) Increased security measures can decrease the amount of
23 retail convenience store crimes.
