25 4-120-103. Minimum increased security measures — Retail convenience
26 store — Definition.
27 (a) As used in this section, "retail convenience store" means a
28 location used by an entity to conduct retail sales of miscellaneous consumer
29 convenience goods to the public.
30 (b) On and after January 1, 2026, a retail convenience store shall:
31 (1) Require a minimum of two (2) employees on the premises of
32 the retail convenience store between the hours of 9:00 p.m. and 6:00 a.m.;
33 (2) Require a security camera system capable of recording and
34 retrieving images to assist in offender identification and apprehension;
35 (3) Have a drop safe or cash management device for restricted
36 access to cash receipts and post a conspicuous notice to this effect at the
